  "name": "Triangle Shot",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are in @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.YG2RxXE9SMfwo6wP]{Monastic Archer Stance} and wielding a bow usable with that stance.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You string three arrows to your bow and fire them all at once. Make three ranged Strikes against a single target with the required weapon, each using your current multiple attack penalty, and you take an additional -2 penalty. This counts as two attacks when calculating your multiple attack penalty, and you combine the attacks' damage for the purpose of resistances and weaknesses.</p>\n<p>Your @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.8bMmGBO6gsMfWZk3]{Stunning Fist} benefit applies to Triangle Shot, even though it isn't a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.nbfNETdpee8CVM17]{Flurry of Blows}. If all three Strikes hit, the target takes @Damage[3d6[bleed]].</p>"
    },
